PRETORIA - Former Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan has hit out at Social Development Minister Bathabile Dlamini, saying she dropped the ball in her handling of the social grants crisis.The Constitutional Court asked Dlamini to explain why she shouldn t pay for the legal costs of the crisis.Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng also questioned how government could have been made to look so incompetent.Dlamini apologised but laid much of the blame for the saga on Sassa CEO Thokozani Magwaza and Treasury.READ: Sassa CEO challenges Dlamini's version on grants crisisSpeaking at a memorial for freedom fighter Ahmed Kathrada, Gordhan didn't mince his words."I never attack a colleague, But today I break that rule," he said."There comes a limit to the lies. Minister Dlamini clearly dropped the ball on grants and must take responsibility, instead of blaming Sassa CEO [and] Treasury. eNCA